HEADWORD: Electro-motion
<hw>E*lec`tro-mo"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The motion
of electricity or its passage from one metal to another in a voltaic
circuit; mechanical action produced by means of electricity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electro-motive</ent>⟦br⟧
